main event: A witness observed a bright, diamond-shaped object emitting a pulsating light in the sky over Davenport, Iowa on March 6, 1969.
interesting points: The object was estimated to be 30-40 feet in diameter and was described as bright and luminous.,The observation lasted approximately 5 minutes before the object accelerated and disappeared.,No sound was reported during the sighting.,The witness immediately contacted local authorities following the sighting.,This report has been forwarded to the Air Force Intelligence Team for further investigation.
witness description: Mr. James Davenport, resident of Davenport, Iowa
